1
00:00:06,370 --> 00:00:07,610
<font color="yellow">(Episode 15)</font>

2
00:00:07,610 --> 00:00:08,640
<font color="yellow">Don't!</font>

3
00:00:12,510 --> 00:00:15,010
<font color="yellow">How do you think your kids will feel if they found out that you died...</font>

4
00:00:16,570 --> 00:00:17,940
<font color="yellow">because of their hospital bills?</font>

5
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:23,240
<font color="yellow">You're only making this choice because you can't handle your life.</font>

6
00:00:24,270 --> 00:00:25,510
<font color="yellow">You're a dad.</font>

7
00:00:26,940 --> 00:00:29,270
<font color="yellow">Do you want to cast a shadow on your kids' lives?</font>

8
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:32,210
<font color="yellow">I won't stop you from dying,</font>

9
00:00:32,770 --> 00:00:35,340
<font color="yellow">but explain to your kids before you kill yourself.</font>

10
00:00:37,540 --> 00:00:39,510
<font color="yellow">Tell them it isn't their fault.</font>

11
00:00:43,870 --> 00:00:47,110
<font color="yellow">No one can replace a dad no matter how much others can help.</font>

12
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:50,740
<font color="yellow">That's how it was for me.</font>

13
00:00:54,840 --> 00:00:56,540
<font color="yellow">I want to die all the time.</font>

14
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:59,040
<font color="yellow">My mother showed me...</font>

15
00:01:03,310 --> 00:01:06,140
<font color="yellow">how to take your own life when you feel cornered.</font>

16
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:11,010
<font color="yellow">Is that what you want...</font>

17
00:01:14,370 --> 00:01:16,070
<font color="yellow">for Hae and Dal?</font>

18
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:31,970
<font color="yellow">Drink this.</font>

19
00:02:39,140 --> 00:02:40,240
<font color="yellow">Where is Mr Nam?</font>

20
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:42,810
<font color="yellow">He'll be with his boys.</font>

21
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,770
<font color="yellow">I'm exhausted.</font>

22
00:02:45,670 --> 00:02:46,810
<font color="yellow">You did well.</font>

23
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:54,540
<font color="yellow">Wounds are so ironic.</font>

24
00:02:56,110 --> 00:02:59,070
<font color="yellow">Your wound helped heal Mr Nam.</font>

25
00:03:00,610 --> 00:03:02,370
<font color="yellow">I guess you could say that.</font>

26
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:03,760
<font color="yellow">Am I wrong?</font>

27
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:06,710
<font color="yellow">I think we helped heal each other.</font>

28
00:03:08,070 --> 00:03:10,210
<font color="yellow">Seeing Mr Nam...</font>

29
00:03:10,210 --> 00:03:12,540
<font color="yellow">reminded me of my dad, and it'd make me feel confused.</font>

30
00:03:13,740 --> 00:03:17,370
<font color="yellow">But now I don't feel so stressed when I think about him.</font>

31
00:03:18,740 --> 00:03:20,240
<font color="yellow">I don't know why. I just do.</font>

32
00:03:20,610 --> 00:03:22,010
<font color="yellow">I know what you mean.</font>

33
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:25,920
<font color="yellow">You can't explain it logically, but you feel at ease.</font>

34
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,010
<font color="yellow">That's it.</font>

35
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:31,540
<font color="yellow">I don't know anything about your childhood.</font>

36
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:35,340
<font color="yellow">What were your parents like?</font>

37
00:03:37,610 --> 00:03:39,070
<font color="yellow">They were both teachers.</font>

38
00:03:40,410 --> 00:03:41,670
<font color="yellow">They both worked,</font>

39
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,750
<font color="yellow">so I came home to an empty house on weekdays.</font>

40
00:03:44,750 --> 00:03:46,770
<font color="yellow">My mom taught at my school,</font>

41
00:03:47,340 --> 00:03:49,770
<font color="yellow">but instead of waiting for her to finish work,</font>

42
00:03:49,770 --> 00:03:50,940
<font color="yellow">I always came home first.</font>

43
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:55,510
<font color="yellow">That bothered me a lot later on.</font>

44
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:58,610
<font color="yellow">Why didn't I wait and come home with her?</font>

45
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:02,610
<font color="yellow">I like doing this.</font>

46
00:04:02,970 --> 00:04:05,240
<font color="yellow">I like it that you like doing this.</font>

47
00:04:16,470 --> 00:04:18,770
<font color="yellow">Tell her to come and see me tomorrow.</font>

48
00:04:19,470 --> 00:04:20,470
<font color="yellow">Yes, Sir.</font>

49
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:25,040
<font color="yellow">(Operating Room)</font>

50
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:30,740
<font color="yellow">Neurosurgeons are sensitive.</font>

51
00:04:31,940 --> 00:04:34,240
<font color="yellow">We always use microscopes when we operate,</font>

52
00:04:34,740 --> 00:04:37,240
<font color="yellow">and operating on parts thinner than paper...</font>

53
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:40,040
<font color="yellow">creates a lot of pressure.</font>

54
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:43,770
<font color="yellow">Our sensitiveness...</font>

55
00:04:44,810 --> 00:04:46,380
<font color="yellow">is our virtue.</font>

56
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,540
<font color="yellow">(Alarm: 5am)</font>

57
00:05:52,070 --> 00:05:53,510
<font color="yellow">You scared me.</font>

58
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:55,370
<font color="yellow">Do you think you're small enough to hide?</font>

59
00:05:56,010 --> 00:05:57,010
<font color="yellow">No.</font>

60
00:06:05,410 --> 00:06:07,370
<font color="yellow">(Dad)</font>

61
00:06:19,310 --> 00:06:22,010
<font color="yellow">The recipient cannot be reached. Please leave...</font>

62
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:24,440
<font color="yellow">Call Seo Woo.</font>

63
00:06:27,110 --> 00:06:29,640
<font color="yellow">What for if she doesn't want to be reached?</font>

64
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,410
<font color="yellow">What kind of a mom says that?</font>

65
00:06:31,940 --> 00:06:33,690
<font color="yellow">I said that because I'm a mom.</font>

66
00:06:33,690 --> 00:06:35,350
<font color="yellow">She isn't ambitious.</font>

67
00:06:35,350 --> 00:06:38,640
<font color="yellow">She did her best until now to live up to your expectations.</font>

68
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:40,920
<font color="yellow">Is this her trying? What did she do?</font>

69
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:43,470
<font color="yellow">What's so hard about following the road I paved?</font>

70
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:46,370
<font color="yellow">The road you paved? Nonsense.</font>

71
00:06:46,370 --> 00:06:47,370
<font color="yellow">What?</font>

72
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:50,840
<font color="yellow">Are you deaf? You heard me.</font>

73
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:53,470
<font color="yellow">I won't help you this time.</font>

74
00:07:03,510 --> 00:07:05,490
<font color="yellow">- What?
-  I'll go in alone.</font>

75
00:07:05,490 --> 00:07:07,340
<font color="yellow">I can't show up with you.</font>

76
00:07:07,340 --> 00:07:09,530
<font color="yellow">It's better if it looks like I caught you...</font>

77
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:12,120
<font color="yellow">rather than you disappeared and no one cared.</font>

78
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:13,210
<font color="yellow">Follow me.</font>

79
00:07:17,970 --> 00:07:19,610
<font color="yellow">How is Nam Dal?</font>

80
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:22,210
<font color="yellow">His ventricle's back to normal,</font>

81
00:07:22,210 --> 00:07:23,770
<font color="yellow">and he has almost no headaches or nausea.</font>

82
00:07:23,770 --> 00:07:25,350
<font color="yellow">He goes home today.</font>

83
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:28,100
<font color="yellow">Being on TV solved their money issue.</font>

84
00:07:28,100 --> 00:07:29,770
<font color="yellow">That's great. You?</font>

85
00:07:39,570 --> 00:07:40,640
<font color="yellow">What are you looking at?</font>

86
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,730
<font color="yellow">Wake up, will you?</font>

87
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:44,240
<font color="yellow">There's so much to do.</font>

88
00:07:44,570 --> 00:07:47,470
<font color="yellow">We need to find Joong Dae. It's been a week.</font>

89
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:50,410
<font color="yellow">He'll be too embarrassed to come back voluntarily.</font>

90
00:07:50,740 --> 00:07:52,430
<font color="yellow">Where on earth is he?</font>

91
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:54,820
<font color="yellow">I called all his close friends...</font>

92
00:07:54,820 --> 00:07:56,010
<font color="yellow">but they haven't seen him.</font>

93
00:07:56,010 --> 00:07:59,570
<font color="yellow">That's why he's the worst kind. He's sneaky and cunning.</font>

94
00:07:59,910 --> 00:08:02,770
<font color="yellow">I wondered why he's in neurosurgery.</font>

95
00:08:03,340 --> 00:08:06,440
<font color="yellow">Turns out he's the typical psycho.</font>

96
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:08,730
<font color="yellow">He might actually become a surgeon.</font>

97
00:08:08,730 --> 00:08:10,210
<font color="yellow">Is that a compliment?</font>

98
00:08:10,210 --> 00:08:11,440
<font color="yellow">Is it a curse?</font>

99
00:08:15,240 --> 00:08:17,370
<font color="yellow">- Joong Dae.
-  Joong Dae.</font>

100
00:08:18,810 --> 00:08:21,610
<font color="yellow">Make him work harder so he's too tired to run off.</font>

101
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:23,570
<font color="yellow">Yes, Doctor.</font>

102
00:08:25,940 --> 00:08:27,110
<font color="yellow">- Joong Dae.
-  Yes?</font>

103
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:29,240
<font color="yellow">Go and check Patient Lee Joo Young's dressing.</font>

104
00:08:29,670 --> 00:08:30,730
<font color="yellow">Okay.</font>

105
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:32,410
<font color="yellow">- Joong Dae.
-  What?</font>

106
00:08:32,410 --> 00:08:33,480
<font color="yellow">Get changed first.</font>

107
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,340
<font color="yellow">Your gown. Did you miss it?</font>

108
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:41,670
<font color="yellow">- Thank you.
-  Work harder.</font>

109
00:08:41,670 --> 00:08:42,670
<font color="yellow">I will.</font>

110
00:08:45,310 --> 00:08:48,040
<font color="yellow">You got fatter. I like that.</font>

111
00:08:50,170 --> 00:08:52,610
<font color="yellow">I'm sending Dal home. What about Hae?</font>

112
00:08:52,610 --> 00:08:54,040
<font color="yellow">He's an outpatient now.</font>

113
00:08:54,040 --> 00:08:55,840
<font color="yellow">Dr Jung discharged him.</font>

114
00:09:08,010 --> 00:09:10,810
<font color="yellow">- What?
-  President Jin wants to see you.</font>

115
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,070
<font color="yellow">I don't.</font>

116
00:09:14,210 --> 00:09:16,910
<font color="yellow">(Receipt)</font>

117
00:09:23,610 --> 00:09:24,610
<font color="yellow">You're here.</font>

118
00:09:24,610 --> 00:09:26,170
<font color="yellow">Hello, Doctors.</font>

119
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:28,900
<font color="yellow">I saw the show.</font>

120
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,370
<font color="yellow">Thanks for everything.</font>

121
00:09:31,010 --> 00:09:32,840
<font color="yellow">I just finished the paperwork.</font>

122
00:09:33,340 --> 00:09:35,980
<font color="yellow">Don't let the boys wash in hot water.</font>

123
00:09:35,980 --> 00:09:39,040
<font color="yellow">Bring them in if they vomit or have headaches.</font>

124
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:40,910
<font color="yellow">I will.</font>

125
00:09:41,340 --> 00:09:42,440
<font color="yellow">I'll check on Dal.</font>

126
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:46,210
<font color="yellow">Excuse me, Dr Yoo.</font>

127
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:47,570
<font color="yellow">I'm happy for you.</font>

128
00:09:47,570 --> 00:09:49,370
<font color="yellow">People are rooting for you,</font>

129
00:09:49,710 --> 00:09:52,210
<font color="yellow">and you don't have to worry about money.</font>

130
00:09:52,210 --> 00:09:53,910
<font color="yellow">I'll remember this forever.</font>

131
00:09:54,370 --> 00:09:56,240
<font color="yellow">Do you think I'm a good person now?</font>

132
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:58,810
<font color="yellow">Yes. I did, then I didn't.</font>

133
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,910
<font color="yellow">You're a good person.</font>

134
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:05,570
<font color="yellow">The world is still a warm place.</font>

135
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:09,810
<font color="yellow">Hae and Dal are lucky to have a dad who loves them.</font>

136
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:10,910
<font color="yellow">Don't say that.</font>

137
00:10:11,770 --> 00:10:13,440
<font color="yellow">All dads are like me.</font>

138
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:20,340
<font color="yellow">My grandmother was one of the biggest reasons...</font>

139
00:10:20,340 --> 00:10:22,410
<font color="yellow">I became a neurosurgeon.</font>

140
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:26,370
<font color="yellow">When I was a troubled child, she once said...</font>

141
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:30,110
<font color="yellow">that being born into this world, you should at least dream big.</font>

142
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,480
<font color="yellow">Can I have the chart?</font>

143
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:36,980
<font color="yellow">You should feel bad if someone died despite your best effort.</font>

144
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,210
<font color="yellow">Does doing your best guarantee forgiveness?</font>

145
00:10:40,210 --> 00:10:43,740
<font color="yellow">If you can prove that I didn't do my best,</font>

146
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:45,610
<font color="yellow">I will accept the accusation.</font>

147
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:49,940
<font color="yellow">Come in.</font>

148
00:10:52,710 --> 00:10:53,740
<font color="yellow">Oh, it's you.</font>

149
00:10:54,140 --> 00:10:55,840
<font color="yellow">Come and have a seat.</font>

150
00:11:00,910 --> 00:11:03,070
<font color="yellow">- Are you busy these days?
-  Yes, a little.</font>

151
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:06,630
<font color="yellow">Why did you need to speak to me? You've been doing this frequently.</font>

152
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:08,570
<font color="yellow">I summoned you once last week, so this is the second time.</font>

153
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:12,610
<font color="yellow">It's only once a week. Does it feel too frequent to you?</font>

154
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:14,610
<font color="yellow">So what would you like to talk to me about?</font>

155
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:16,240
<font color="yellow">Nothing special.</font>

156
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:20,240
<font color="yellow">I just want to see you from time to time and remind myself to work hard.</font>

157
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,410
<font color="yellow">We tend to become lazy as we get old.</font>

158
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:28,210
<font color="yellow">(Neurosurgery, Choi Kang Soo)</font>

159
00:11:28,740 --> 00:11:31,880
<font color="yellow">I'll get back to work. I think they need me at the emergency room.</font>

160
00:11:31,880 --> 00:11:32,970
<font color="yellow">Yes, go ahead.</font>

161
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:36,110
<font color="yellow">How is Seo Woo doing?</font>

162
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:42,110
<font color="yellow">You should talk to her directly instead of asking me about her.</font>

163
00:11:42,110 --> 00:11:43,170
<font color="yellow">Well, then.</font>

164
00:11:48,370 --> 00:11:50,740
<font color="yellow">Oh, you're the one who was on television.</font>

165
00:11:51,310 --> 00:11:53,310
<font color="yellow">- I enjoyed the show.
-  Thank you.</font>

166
00:11:59,540 --> 00:12:00,640
<font color="yellow">I like her.</font>

167
00:12:02,070 --> 00:12:04,570
<font color="yellow">I got many calls from my friends after that show aired.</font>

168
00:12:05,070 --> 00:12:07,510
<font color="yellow">Use it to promote the hospital.</font>

169
00:12:08,170 --> 00:12:10,240
<font color="yellow">I want to fire her, but I can't do it because of it.</font>

170
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,810
<font color="yellow">- Why do you want to fire her?
-  You don't need to know.</font>

171
00:12:13,570 --> 00:12:16,500
<font color="yellow">Ji Hong is signing the investment contract today, isn't he?</font>

172
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:17,510
<font color="yellow">I think so.</font>

173
00:12:18,540 --> 00:12:20,910
<font color="yellow">He'll try to do something with it, but it won't work.</font>

174
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:25,070
<font color="yellow">He'll find out that he's just a clueless frog in his little pond.</font>

175
00:12:26,370 --> 00:12:29,230
<font color="yellow">Gosh, how can something like this happen? Thank you anyway.</font>

176
00:12:29,230 --> 00:12:30,240
<font color="yellow">No problem.</font>

177
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:34,210
<font color="yellow">The patient is a 27-year-old male. Due to a gas explosion, a battery...</font>

178
00:12:34,210 --> 00:12:36,840
<font color="yellow">at the construction site got stuck in his eyes. On the CT scan...</font>

179
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:38,860
<font color="yellow">- A battery?
-  Yes.</font>

180
00:12:38,860 --> 00:12:40,840
<font color="yellow">- What's his mental status?
-  He seems alert.</font>

181
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:42,310
<font color="yellow">Let's go.</font>

182
00:12:43,470 --> 00:12:46,340
<font color="yellow">- Please stop moving. Stay still.
-  My eyes!</font>

183
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:50,210
<font color="yellow">- You're here.
-  Sir, can you hear me?</font>

184
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:51,810
<font color="yellow">Yes, I can.</font>

185
00:12:52,740 --> 00:12:54,840
<font color="yellow">But I'm in so much pain, Doctor.</font>

186
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:57,210
<font color="yellow">Please calm down. Could you raise your right arm?</font>

187
00:12:57,610 --> 00:12:58,670
<font color="yellow">Yes.</font>

188
00:13:00,110 --> 00:13:01,140
<font color="yellow">Now, your left leg.</font>

189
00:13:04,340 --> 00:13:05,340
<font color="yellow">Just a second, please.</font>

190
00:13:08,910 --> 00:13:10,510
<font color="yellow">His pupil reflex and motor ability are normal.</font>

191
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,730
<font color="yellow">Let's take an X-ray right now. Call Prof. Hong.</font>

192
00:13:12,730 --> 00:13:15,350
<font color="yellow">He's off until this afternoon.</font>

193
00:13:15,350 --> 00:13:16,440
<font color="yellow">Why?</font>

194
00:13:28,210 --> 00:13:29,770
<font color="yellow">- It's very nice to meet you.
-  Hello.</font>

195
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:31,710
<font color="yellow">Nice to meet you.</font>

196
00:13:33,370 --> 00:13:34,640
<font color="yellow">Hello.</font>

197
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,910
<font color="yellow">- I'm happy to meet you in person.
-  Nice to meet you.</font>

198
00:13:36,410 --> 00:13:37,770
<font color="yellow">- This way, please.
-  Okay.</font>

199
00:13:51,310 --> 00:13:52,370
<font color="yellow">(Hong Ji Hong)</font>

200
00:13:54,310 --> 00:13:56,350
<font color="yellow">- Thank you.
-  Thank you.</font>

201
00:13:56,350 --> 00:14:00,070
<font color="yellow">(Park Hyun Joon)</font>

202
00:14:08,740 --> 00:14:11,530
<font color="yellow">The battery pierced the upper walls of the eye socket in his left eye.</font>

203
00:14:11,530 --> 00:14:13,010
<font color="yellow">It caused intracerebral haemorrhage...</font>

204
00:14:13,010 --> 00:14:14,470
<font color="yellow">and extradural haemorrhage in the frontal lobe.</font>

205
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:17,600
<font color="yellow">We should work on this with Ophthalmology.</font>

206
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:19,700
<font color="yellow">I already called them. They're on their way.</font>

207
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:22,610
<font color="yellow">We'll go in after Ophthalmology removes the battery.</font>

208
00:14:23,470 --> 00:14:25,530
<font color="yellow">Fortunately, it doesn't look like there's too much bleeding.</font>

209
00:14:25,530 --> 00:14:28,770
<font color="yellow">It doesn't look like the dura mater is torn. Let's hope it's the case.</font>

210
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:31,240
<font color="yellow">Book an OR first.</font>

